```
# 詞: 銀包

1. 我出門口嗰陣唔記得拎銀包，搞到而家連搭巴士都冇錢。 (I forgot to take my wallet when I left home, and now I don't even have money to take the bus.)
2. 呢個銀包係我女朋友送俾我嘅生日禮物，所以我好珍惜。 (This wallet is a birthday gift from my girlfriend, so I cherish it very much.)
3. 佢搭地鐵嗰陣俾人扒手偷咗個銀包，入面有晒佢啲證件同信用卡。 (His wallet was stolen by a pickpocket while he was taking the MTR, with all his ID cards and credit cards inside.)
4. 呢個名牌銀包好靚，但係價錢太貴啦，我買唔落手。 (This branded wallet is very pretty, but the price is too high, I can't bring myself to buy it.)
5. 你有冇見到我個銀包呀？我搵咗成朝都搵唔到。 (Have you seen my wallet? I've been looking for it all morning and still can't find it.)
6. 佢個銀包入面得番十蚊紙，真係搵鬼食都唔夠啦。 (He only has a ten-dollar bill left in his wallet, which is definitely not enough for even a decent meal.)
7. 我尋日喺街邊執到個銀包，已經交咗去差館㗎啦。 (I found a wallet on the street yesterday, and I've already handed it in to the police station.)
8. 落雨嗰院唔好將銀包擺喺褸袋，好容易整濕㗎。 (Don't put your wallet in your coat pocket when it's raining; it can easily get wet.)
9. 佢每次買完嘢都會將啲散紙塞晒入銀包度，搞到個銀包脹到似塊磚頭。 (Every time after buying things, he stuffs all the loose change into his wallet, making it as bloated as a brick.)
10. 呢個銀包用咗五年都未爛，質素真係冇得頂！ (This wallet hasn't worn out after five years of use; the quality is absolutely top-notch!)
``` [end of text]


